&lt;p&gt;What is the best way to compare objects in JavaScript?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; user1 = {name : &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;nerd&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;org&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;dev&quot;&lt;/span&gt;};
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; user2 = {name : &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;nerd&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;org&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;dev&quot;&lt;/span&gt;};
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; eq = user1 == user2;
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;(eq); &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// gives false&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I know that &lt;strong&gt;two objects are equal if they refer to the exact same object&lt;/strong&gt;, but is there a way to check if they have the same attributes&apos; values?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following way works for me, but is it the only possibility?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; eq = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title class_&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;toJSON&lt;/span&gt;(user1) == &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title class_&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;toJSON&lt;/span&gt;(user2);
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;(eq); &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// gives true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
